Fish Welfare Initiative Data Review¶

Objective¶

Review data quality and data trends to gain insights into M&E campaign

Dataset¶

The dataset contains the following features:

  • JotForm Entry ID : JotForm Entry ID : int
  • Observer ID : Observer ID : int
  • Date : Date : date
  • Pond ID : Pond ID : Alpha numeric
  • Morning or Evening : Type of Measurement : Descriptive
  • Time : Time : Military time
  • Meter : Meter : Descriptive
  • Follow up Measurement? : Follow up Measurement? : Yes, No
  • DO (mg/L) : Dissolved Oxygen (DO) average in mg/L : float
  • Temp (C) : Temperature average in Celsius : float
  • pH : pH average : float
  • Ammonia (mg/L) : Ammonia average in mg/L : float
  • Turbidity (cm) : Turbidity average in cm (via Secchi disk) : float
  • Salinity (ppt) : Salinity in ppt : float
  • TDS (ppt) : Total Dissolved Solids in ppt : float
  • Sun : Weather : Sun : Descriptive
  • Clouds : Weather : Clouds : Descriptive
  • Rain : Weather : Rain : Descriptive
  • Wind : Wind : Descriptive
  • Quality in range? : Is water quality in the required range? : Yes, No
  • Parameter(s) OOR : Which parameter(s) is/are out of range? : Descriptive
  • CA Requested : Farmer : Corrective actions requested from the farmer : Descriptive
  • CA Taken? : Farmer : Did the farmer implement the corrective actions? : Yes, No
  • Correct CA Taken? : Farmer : Did the farmer implement the corrective actions for achieving ideal ranges? : Yes, No
  • CA Actual : Farmer : Corrective actions taken by the farmer : Descriptive
  • CA Difficulty : Farmer : How did the farmer find implementing the corrective actions? : Descriptive
  • Post CA improvement? : Did the targeted water quality parameters improve to the required range after the implementation of corrective actions? : Yes, No
  • Reason for inaction : Farmer : If the farmer didn't apply corrective actions what were the reasons? : Descriptive
  • Stocking Density (fish/acre) : Stocking density per acre : int
  • Daily feed (kg) : How much feed does the farmer give per day in kg? : float
  • Disease outbreak? : Is this pond currently experiencing a disease outbreak? : Yes, No
  • Lice infestation? : Is this pond currently having a lice infestation? : Yes, No
  • Feeding behavior : Feeding : int
  • Air gulping extent : Air gulping : int
  • Tail splashing extent : Tail splashing : int
  • Farmer dead fish (15 day count) : How many dead fish did the FARMER find in the last 15 days? : int
  • FWI dead fish count : How many dead fish did FWI find during their visit? : int
  • FWI impact noted : Did we help the fish at this pond per our definition? : Yes, No
  • Description of impact : How did we help the fish? : Descriptive
  • How many fish did we help? : How many fish did we help? : Int
  • Primary Productivity GPP (mg/L) : Primary Productivity GPP in mg/L : float
  • Light bottle DO NPP : Light bottle DO NPP : float
  • Dark bottle DO R : Dark bottle DO R : float
  • Water color : Water Color : Descriptive
  • PP (mg/L) : PP in mg/L : float
  • Pond locations visited : How many locations will you visit at this pond? : int
  • T1 (C) : Reader 1 : Temperature in Celsius : float
  • DO1 (mg/L) : Reader 1 : Dissolved Oxygen in mg/L : float
  • pH1 : Reader 1 : pH : float
  • T2 (C) : Reader 2 : Temperature in Celsius : float
  • DO2 (mg/L) : Reader 2 -Dissolved Oxygen in mg/L : float
  • pH2 : Reader 2 : pH : float
  • T3 (C) : Reader 3 : Temperature in Celsius : float
  • DO3 (mg/L) : Reader 3 : Dissolved Oxygen in mg/L : float
  • pH3 : Reader 3 : pH : float
  • Notes : 1 : Notes : 1 : Descriptive
  • Notes : 2 : Notes : 2 : Descriptive
  • Notes : 3 : Notes : 3 : Descriptive
  • Notes : 4 : Notes : 4 : Descriptive
  • Notes : 5 : Notes : 5 : Descriptive
  • Submission Date : Submission Date : Date

In [12]:
# Create summary table

# Filter for control columns
df_control = df.loc[df['control_pond'] == 0]

agg_df = df_control.groupby('Pond ID').agg(
             date_start = ('Date','min'),
             date_end = ('Date','min'),
             date_range=('Date', lambda x: x.max() - x.min()),
             QIR_mean = ('QIR', 'mean'), # Percent of measurements where water quality was in range 
             QIR_count = ('QIR', 'count'),
             DO_mean=('DO (mg/L)', 'mean'),
             pH_mean=('pH', 'mean'),
             Ammonia_mean = ('Ammonia (mg/L)','mean'),
             Turbidity_mean = ('Turbidity (cm)','mean'),
             Salinity_mean = ('Salinity (ppt)','mean'),
             CA_count = ('CA','sum') # count of corrective actions
).sort_values(by='QIR_mean',ascending=False)

Notes¶

Correlations noted:¶

  • Number of fish helped: TDS, Salinity, Ammonia, Tail splashing
  • Temp, DO, Ammonia and pH
  • Stocking density is negatively correlated with the number of fish helped

# Create hystograms of water quality parameters 

parameter = 'DO (mg/L)' # Options: 'DO (mg/L)', 'Temp (C)', 'pH', 'Ammonia (mg/L)', 'Turbidity (cm)', 'Salinity (ppt)', 'TDS (ppt)', 'Sun', 'Stocking Density (fish/acre)', 'Daily feed (kg)', 'Feeding behaviour', 'Air gulping extent', 'Tail splashing extent', 'Farmer dead fish (15 day count)', 'FWI dead fish count', 'How many fish did we help?', 'Primary Productivity GPP (mg/L)', 'Light bottle DO NPP', 'Dark bottle DO R', 'PP (mg/L)', 'Pond locations visited'
title1 = parameter +' - Treatment Ponds'
title2 = parameter +' - Control Ponds'

sns.histplot(data=df.loc[df['control_pond'] == 0], x=parameter,stat='density', discrete= True, hue="Morning or Evening",hue_order=["Morning", "Evening"], kde=True).set(title=title1)

# Set parameters for histogram 
parameter = 'DO (mg/L)' # Options: 'DO (mg/L)', 'Temp (C)', 'pH', 'Ammonia (mg/L)', 'Turbidity (cm)', 'Salinity (ppt)', 'TDS (ppt)', 'Sun', 'Stocking Density (fish/acre)', 'Daily feed (kg)', 'Feeding behaviour', 'Air gulping extent', 'Tail splashing extent', 'Farmer dead fish (15 day count)', 'FWI dead fish count', 'How many fish did we help?', 'Primary Productivity GPP (mg/L)', 'Light bottle DO NPP', 'Dark bottle DO R', 'PP (mg/L)', 'Pond locations visited'
Daytime = 'Morning' # Morning or Evening 
control = 0 # zero for treatment point, one for control pond
title = 'Dissolved Oxygen - Treatment Ponds (Morning Only) \n Ideal Range: 4 - 5 mg/L \n Required Range: 3 - 5 mg/L'

df_new=df.loc[(df['Morning or Evening'].values == Daytime) & (df['control_pond'] == control)]

sns.histplot(data=df_new, x=parameter,  hue="Morning or Evening",kde=True).set(title=title)

parameter = 'DO (mg/L)' # Options: 'DO (mg/L)', 'Temp (C)', 'pH', 'Ammonia (mg/L)', 'Turbidity (cm)', 'Salinity (ppt)', 'TDS (ppt)', 'Sun', 'Stocking Density (fish/acre)', 'Daily feed (kg)', 'Feeding behaviour', 'Air gulping extent', 'Tail splashing extent', 'Farmer dead fish (15 day count)', 'FWI dead fish count', 'How many fish did we help?', 'Primary Productivity GPP (mg/L)', 'Light bottle DO NPP', 'Dark bottle DO R', 'PP (mg/L)', 'Pond locations visited'

control = 0 # zero for treatment point, 1 for control pond
title='Dissolved Oxygen - Treatment Ponds (Morning Only) \n Ideal Range: 4 - 5 mg/L \n Required Range: 3 - 5 mg/L'


df_new=df.loc[(df['Morning or Evening'].values == Daytime) & (df['control_pond'] == 0)]

plt.xticks(rotation=90);

Notes on Morning DO levels:¶

  • Ideal Range 4 - 5 mg/L
  • Required Range 3 - 5 mg/L
  • The histogram shows that the data is bifurcated at 3 mg/L, with a sizable portion of the data below 3 mg/L.
  • The morning box plots by pond shows that a number of treatment ponds have low dissolved oxegen.
  • Very few ponds are in the ideal range.

Notes on Turbidity:¶

  • Ideal Range 30 - 40 cm
  • Required Range 15 - 50 cm
  • Measurement time of day does not have a bearing on turbidity.
  • Control ponds show similar turbidity levels.
  • Most ponds do not fall within the ideal range but they do fall within the required range.
  • A few ponds are outliers on the high end, i.e., > 40 cm.

Next steps: Investigate the impact of actions taken¶

Actions taken:¶

  • Quality in range? : Is water quality in the required range? : Yes, No
  • Parameter(s) OOR : Which parameter(s) is/are out of range? : Descriptive
  • CA Requested : Farmer : Corrective actions requested from the farmer : Descriptive
  • CA Taken? : Farmer : Did the farmer implement the corrective actions? : Yes, No
  • Correct CA Taken? : Farmer : Did the farmer implement the corrective actions for achieving ideal ranges? : Yes, No
  • CA Actual : Farmer : Corrective actions taken by the farmer : Descriptive
  • CA Difficulty : Farmer : How did the farmer find implementing the corrective actions? : Descriptive
  • Post CA improvement? : Did the targeted water quality parameters improve to the required range after the implementation of - - - corrective actions? : Yes, No
